            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In n(omine) D(omini). C(on)stat me <persName key="#Abbots"><name
                                ref="Richardus">Richardus</name></persName> gr(aci)a D(e)i <rs
                            key="#Abbots">abb(as)</rs> reg(u)l(e) <rs key="#Monasteries"
                            >mon(asterii)</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/1487">S(an)c(t)i
                            Apollinaris q(ui) v(ocatur) Novo</orgName> accepisse(m) accepi a vob(is)
                                <persName><name ref="Apollinaris">Apollinaris</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Rent_in_money">pensionem</rs> p(ro) <rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                            >tribu[s] unciis in int(e)g(ro)</rs> q(ue) sunt posite in <rs
                            key="#Fundi">fundo</rs> q(ui) voc(atur) <geogName key="#Fundi"
                            ref="#estates/2421"><placeName key="#Fundi"
                            >Colopedio</placeName></geogName> cu(m) om(n)ib(us) sibi
                        p(er)tinentib(us), <rs key="#Fines">territorio</rs> <geogName key="#Fundi #Fines"><placeName
                            key="#Fundi #Fines" ref="#places/3515"
                            >Liviense</placeName></geogName>, <rs key="#Plebs">plebe</rs> <orgName key="#Plebs" ref="#juridical_persons/1488">S(an)c(t)e Reparate</orgName>, quas
                        p(er) <rs key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis"
                            >enfiteusin</rs> t[en]ere videt[is] ad(e) iura s(uprascrip)ti m[o]n(asterii)
                        n(ost)ri, et p(er) unaquaq(ue) indic(ione) de[n]arii q(ui)nq(ue) tantu(m).
                        Und(e) p(ro) munimine v(est)ro feci vob(is) hoc [d]eaccepto in m(en)se
                        marcio, indicc(ione) decima, <placeName ref="#places/594">Raven(ne)</placeName>. In n(omine) D(omi)ni. Ego
                        Richa[r]d[us] p(res)b(i)t(er) et mon(achus) [atque abbas regule]
                        mon(a)s(terii) S(an)c(t)i Apoll[inaris qui vocatur Novo] in hoc de[accepto]
                        manus meas s(ub)s(cripsi) p(er) indic(ione) undecima.</ab>
